910
00:53:55,381 --> 00:53:58,300
We never told the truth
for ten minutes in this house.

911
00:53:58,384 --> 00:54:01,260
- We always told truth.
- Are you the assistant buyer?

912
00:54:01,261 --> 00:54:03,971
You're one of
the two assistants to the assistant.

913
00:54:03,972 --> 00:54:06,641
- I'm practically...
- You are practically full of it.

914
00:54:06,642 --> 00:54:08,935
- We all are. I'm through with it.
- Yeah.

915
00:54:08,936 --> 00:54:11,871
- Hear this, Willy. This is me.
- I know you.

916
00:54:12,106 --> 00:54:14,982
Do you know why I had no
address for three months?

917
00:54:14,983 --> 00:54:17,693
I stole a suit in Kansas City
and I was in gaol.

918
00:54:17,694 --> 00:54:21,031
- I suppose it's my fault.
- Stop crying, I'm through with it!

919
00:54:21,115 --> 00:54:24,243
I stole myself
out of every good job since high school.

920
00:54:24,326 --> 00:54:25,743
Whose fault is that?

921
00:54:25,744 --> 00:54:29,081
I could never get anywhere
'cause you blew me so full of hot air

922
00:54:29,206 --> 00:54:32,041
that I could never stand
taking orders from anybody.

923
00:54:32,042 --> 00:54:34,335
- I hear that.
- Stop it!

924
00:54:34,336 --> 00:54:37,172
I had to be boss big shot
in two weeks and I'm through.

925
00:54:37,256 --> 00:54:39,674
- Then hang yourself for spite!
- No! No!

926
00:54:39,675 --> 00:54:43,470
No, nobody is hanging himself, Willy.

927
00:54:46,598 --> 00:54:51,145
I ran down 11 flights with a pen
in my hand today.

928
00:54:51,228 --> 00:54:53,563
And suddenly I stopped.
Do you hear me?

929
00:54:53,564 --> 00:54:56,900
In the middle of that office building...
Do you hear this?

930
00:54:56,984 --> 00:54:59,110
I stopped...

931
00:54:59,111 --> 00:55:03,157
...in the middle of the building
and I saw the sky!

932
00:55:03,240 --> 00:55:09,121
And I... I... I saw the things
that I love in this world.

933
00:55:09,246 --> 00:55:12,691
The work and the food

934
00:55:12,875 --> 00:55:15,711
and the time to sit and smoke.

935
00:55:15,794 --> 00:55:20,132
I looked at that pen in my hand and
I said, "What am I grabbing this for?

936
00:55:20,215 --> 00:55:22,925
Why am I trying to become
what I don't want to be?

937
00:55:22,926 --> 00:55:24,594
What am I doing in an office?

938
00:55:24,595 --> 00:55:27,723
Making a contemptuous begging
fool of myself,

939
00:55:27,806 --> 00:55:30,558
when all that I want
is out there waiting for me?"

940
00:55:30,559 --> 00:55:33,896
The minute I say it, I know who I am.
Why can't I say that, Willy?

941
00:55:33,979 --> 00:55:35,980
The door to your life is wide open!

942
00:55:35,981 --> 00:55:38,482
Pop, I am a dime a dozen and so are you.

943
00:55:38,483 --> 00:55:41,110
I am not a dime a dozen!

944
00:55:41,111 --> 00:55:44,072
I am Willy Loman and you are Biff Loman!

945
00:55:44,156 --> 00:55:47,959
I am not the leader of men, Willy!
And neither are you!

946
00:55:48,160 --> 00:55:51,622
You were never anything
but a hard-working drummer

947
00:55:51,747 --> 00:55:54,582
who landed in the ashcan
like all the rest of them.

948
00:55:54,583 --> 00:55:57,209
I am one dollar an hour, Willy!

949
00:55:57,210 --> 00:56:00,923
I am not bringing home
any prizes anymore,

950
00:56:01,006 --> 00:56:03,174
and you're gonna stop waiting for me!

951
00:56:03,175 --> 00:56:07,012
- You vengeful, spiteful mutt!
- Yeah, Pop!

952
00:56:07,095 --> 00:56:10,057
Pop, I'm nothing.

953
00:56:10,140 --> 00:56:13,226
I'm nothing, Pop.
Can't you understand that?

954
00:56:13,310 --> 00:56:15,645
There's no spite in it anymore.

955
00:56:15,646 --> 00:56:18,539
I'm just what I am, that's all.

956
00:56:20,192 --> 00:56:23,528
What are you doing?
Aw, what are you doing?

957
00:56:28,367 --> 00:56:31,620
- Why is he crying?
- Dad...

958
00:56:32,829 --> 00:56:35,556
Will you let me go, for God's sake?

959
00:56:36,500 --> 00:56:41,838
Will you take that phoney dream
and burn it before something happens?

960
00:57:21,211 --> 00:57:24,105
I'll go in the morning.

961
00:57:27,801 --> 00:57:30,111
Put him to bed.

962
00:57:37,185 --> 00:57:41,231
Isn't that...
Isn't that remarkable?

963
00:57:42,315 --> 00:57:45,152
Biff, he...

964
00:57:46,778 --> 00:57:49,672
He likes me.

965
00:57:49,948 --> 00:57:53,618
- He loves you, Willy.
- Always did, Pop.

966
00:57:53,702 --> 00:57:56,370
Aw, Biff, he...

967
00:57:56,371 --> 00:57:59,140
He cried. He cried to me.

968
00:57:59,583 --> 00:58:03,211
Aw, that boy.
That boy, he's going to be magnificent.

969
00:58:04,337 --> 00:58:07,131
Yes, outstanding,
with 20,000 behind him.

970
00:58:07,132 --> 00:58:09,675
Come to bed, Willy.
It's all settled now.

971
00:58:09,676 --> 00:58:13,096
Oh, yes, we'll sleep.
Come on, let's go to sleep.

972
00:58:13,221 --> 00:58:15,806
It takes a great man
to crack thejungle.

973
00:58:15,807 --> 00:58:19,144
I'm getting married.
Don't forget. I'm changing everything.

974
00:58:19,227 --> 00:58:22,189
I'm gonna run that department
before the year is up.

975
00:58:22,272 --> 00:58:24,857
Thejungle is dark
but full of diamonds.

976
00:58:24,858 --> 00:58:28,361
Be good. You're both good boys.
Just act that way, that's all.

977
00:58:29,863 --> 00:58:32,373
- Night, Pop.
- Night, boy.

978
00:58:33,241 --> 00:58:36,785
- Come, dear. -S hh. One must
go in to fetch a diamond out.

979
00:58:36,786 --> 00:58:39,496
I just want to get settled down
for a little while.

980
00:58:39,497 --> 00:58:42,626
- I want you upstairs.
- A few minutes. I couldn't sleep now.

981
00:58:42,751 --> 00:58:45,629
- Go. You look awful tired.
- Not like an appointment.

982
00:58:45,712 --> 00:58:48,757
- A diamond is rough and hard to touch.
- I'll be right up.

983
00:58:48,882 --> 00:58:51,718
- I think it's the only way.
- Sure, it's the best thing.

984
00:58:51,801 --> 00:58:56,665
Best thing. The only way.
Everything is gonna be...

985
00:58:56,848 --> 00:58:59,825
Aw, go on, kid. Get to bed.

986
00:59:00,802 --> 00:59:05,265
- You look so tired. - Now, you
come right up. - Two minutes.

987
00:59:13,815 --> 00:59:16,901
Loves me. Always loved me.
Isn't that a remarkable thing?

988
00:59:16,985 --> 00:59:21,322
- Ben, he'll worship me for it.
- It's dark there.

989
00:59:21,406 --> 00:59:23,198
But full of diamonds, Willy.

990
00:59:23,199 --> 00:59:26,995
Can you imagine that magnificence
with $20,000 in his pocket?

991
00:59:27,078 --> 00:59:29,204
Willy, come up.

992
00:59:29,205 --> 00:59:31,957
Yes, yes, coming, coming!

993
00:59:32,058 --> 00:59:35,019
It's very smart,
you realise, don't you, sweetheart?

994
00:59:35,103 --> 00:59:36,895
Even Ben sees it.

995
00:59:36,896 --> 00:59:39,415
I gotta go, baby.

996
00:59:43,069 --> 00:59:45,254
Bye-bye.

997
00:59:45,863 --> 00:59:48,700
When the mail comes
he'll be ahead of Bernard again.

998
00:59:48,783 --> 00:59:53,328
- A perfect proposition all around.
- Did you see how he cried to me?

999
00:59:53,329 --> 00:59:57,357
- Aw, I could kiss him, Ben.
- Time, William, time.

1000
00:59:57,458 --> 01:00:01,546
Ben, I always knew one way or another
we were gonna make it, Biff and I.

1001
01:00:01,629 --> 01:00:04,924
Boat! We'll be late.

1002
01:00:06,384 --> 01:00:11,639
Now, when you kick off,
I want a 70 yard boot.

1003
01:00:11,723 --> 01:00:15,268
And get right down the field
under the ball.

1004
01:00:15,351 --> 01:00:18,688
And when you hit,
hit low and hit hard,

1005
01:00:18,813 --> 01:00:21,189
because it's important, boy.

1006
01:00:21,190 --> 01:00:25,319
There's all kinds of
important people in the stands.

1007
01:00:26,195 --> 01:00:28,922
The first thing that you know...

1008
01:00:29,282 --> 01:00:30,782
Willy?

1009
01:00:30,783 --> 01:00:33,703
- Ben? Ben, where do I...?
- Willy?

1010
01:00:33,786 --> 01:00:37,874
- Ben! Ben!
- Willy!

1011
01:00:38,958 --> 01:00:40,667
Shh. Shh.

1012
01:00:40,668 --> 01:00:43,420
Shh! Shh!

1013
01:00:43,421 --> 01:00:46,482
- Willy, please come up.
- Oh.

1014
01:00:48,426 --> 01:00:50,652
- Willy!
- Shh!

1015
01:00:55,099 --> 01:00:57,159
Willy?

1016
01:00:59,687 --> 01:01:03,190
- Pop?
- Willy, answer me!

1017
01:01:03,191 --> 01:01:06,502
Willy!

1018
01:01:07,962 --> 01:01:11,883
- Willy!
- Pop! No!

1019
01:01:12,758 --> 01:01:15,444
- No!
- No!

1020
01:01:19,432 --> 01:01:23,603
It's getting dark, Linda.

1021
01:01:25,146 --> 01:01:29,442
How about it, Ma? Better get
some rest. They'll be closing the gates.

1022
01:01:29,567 --> 01:01:32,612
He had no right to do that.
There was no necessity.

1023
01:01:32,695 --> 01:01:35,615
- We would have helped him.
- Come on.

1024
01:01:35,698 --> 01:01:39,909
- Why didn't anybody come?
- It was a very nice funeral.

1025
01:01:39,910 --> 01:01:43,122
Where were the people he knew?
Maybe they blame him.

1026
01:01:43,205 --> 01:01:46,584
It's a rough world, Linda.
They wouldn't blame him.

1027
01:01:46,667 --> 01:01:51,664
I can't understand it.
First time in just about 35 years

1028
01:01:52,048 --> 01:01:55,593
we were almost free and clear.

1029
01:01:56,844 --> 01:02:00,030
He only needed a little salary.

1030
01:02:00,097 --> 01:02:03,059
He was even finished with the dentist.

1031
01:02:03,142 --> 01:02:06,145
No man only needs a little salary.

1032
01:02:07,730 --> 01:02:09,689
I can't understand it.

1033
01:02:09,690 --> 01:02:15,154
There were a lot of nice days when he'd
come home from a trip or on Sundays,

1034
01:02:15,237 --> 01:02:18,616
making the stoop,
finishing the cellar

1035
01:02:18,699 --> 01:02:22,870
when he built the extra bathroom
and put up the garage.

1036
01:02:24,288 --> 01:02:27,875
You know, Charley, I think there was
more of him in that front stoop

1037
01:02:27,958 --> 01:02:30,293
than in all the sales he ever made.

1038
01:02:30,294 --> 01:02:34,590
Yep. He was a happy man
with a bunch of cement.

1039
01:02:34,673 --> 01:02:37,509
He was wonderful with his hands.

1040
01:02:37,510 --> 01:02:40,763
He had the wrong dreams.
AII, all wrong.

1041
01:02:40,846 --> 01:02:44,107
Don't say that.
The man didn't know who he was.

1042
01:02:44,308 --> 01:02:47,185
Nobody dast blame this man.

1043
01:02:47,186 --> 01:02:49,579
You don't understand.

1044
01:02:49,980 --> 01:02:52,916
Willy was a salesman.

1045
01:02:53,484 --> 01:02:56,320
For a salesman,
there is no rock bottom to the life.

1046
01:02:56,403 --> 01:02:58,279
He don't put a bolt to a nut,

1047
01:02:58,280 --> 01:03:01,074
he don't tell you the law,
don't give you medicine.

1048
01:03:01,075 --> 01:03:03,911
He's a man way out there in the blue,

1049
01:03:05,204 --> 01:03:08,056
riding on a smile and a shoeshine.

1050
01:03:08,541 --> 01:03:13,219
When they start not smiling back,
that's an earthquake.

1051
01:03:13,420 --> 01:03:17,174
You get yourself a couple of spots
on your hat and you're finished.

1052
01:03:18,968 --> 01:03:22,028
Nobody dast blame this man.

1053
01:03:22,388 --> 01:03:25,916
A salesman has got to dream, boy.
Comes with the territory.

1054
01:03:26,100 --> 01:03:30,019
- The man didn't know who he was.
- Don't say that!

1055
01:03:30,020 --> 01:03:33,039
Why don't you come with me, Happy?

1056
01:03:33,649 --> 01:03:36,126
I'm not licked that easily.

1057
01:03:36,485 --> 01:03:39,738
I'm staying right in the city
and I'm gonna beat this racquet.

1058
01:03:41,490 --> 01:03:44,159
- Loman brothers.
- I know who I am, kid.

1059
01:03:44,160 --> 01:03:46,911
All right, boy,
I'm gonna show you and everybody

1060
01:03:46,912 --> 01:03:50,374
that Willy Loman did not die in vain.
He had a good dream.

1061
01:03:50,457 --> 01:03:53,752
It's the only dream you can have,
to come out number one man.

1062
01:03:53,836 --> 01:03:57,514
He fought it out here and this is where
I'm gonna win it for him.

1063
01:04:00,050 --> 01:04:02,777
Oh, I'll be with you in just a minute.

1064
01:04:03,095 --> 01:04:05,855
You go on, Charley.

1065
01:04:06,140 --> 01:04:08,783
Just... just a minute.

1066
01:04:13,147 --> 01:04:16,416
I never had a chance to say good-bye.

1067
01:04:25,618 --> 01:04:28,277
Help me, Willy.

1068
01:04:28,495 --> 01:04:30,972
I can't cry.

1069
01:04:31,582 --> 01:04:36,503
Seems to me you're just away on
another trip and I keep expecting you.

1070
01:04:38,964 --> 01:04:41,574
Why did you do it?

1071
01:04:42,968 --> 01:04:45,846
I search and I search,

1072
01:04:46,972 --> 01:04:49,808
and I search,

1073
01:04:51,143 --> 01:04:56,106
and I can't understand it, Willy.

1074
01:04:59,318 --> 01:05:02,921
I made the last payment
on the house today.

1075
01:05:04,448 --> 01:05:06,841
Today!

1076
01:05:14,083 --> 01:05:17,319
And there'll be nobody home.

1077
01:05:19,463 --> 01:05:22,757
We're free and clear.

1078
01:05:26,762 --> 01:05:29,272
We're free.

1079
01:05:30,057 --> 01:05:32,575
We're free.

1080
01:05:37,272 --> 01:05:40,000
We're free.